{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17508608","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17508608"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T12:07:57+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T12:07:57+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2813"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"2813","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2813"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.01,0.26,0.01,0.38,0.34]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2791"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107894"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2791","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2791"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2813"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90310"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"2287"},{"type":"tags","id":"4974"},{"type":"tags","id":"4977"},{"type":"tags","id":"4988"},{"type":"tags","id":"11626"},{"type":"tags","id":"11633"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"3756"},{"type":"contributions","id":"3757"},{"type":"contributions","id":"3777"},{"type":"contributions","id":"16646"},{"type":"contributions","id":"33821"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107894","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/107894"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 64-year-old woman presents to her General Practitioner for a routine health check. She is currently enjoying reasonably good health, but her medical history includes rheumatoid arthritis, hypertension, hyperlipidaemia and obesity. Her current medications include methotrexate, perindopril, simvastatin. She also takes calcium, vitamin D and folate supplements. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHer physical examination, apart from her obesity, is unremarkable. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EShe asks, with winter approaching, if she should have any vaccinations - in addition to one for COVID. She completed her childhood vaccinations however has not had any vaccinations in the last five years.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following vaccination regimens would be most appropriate?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["No other vaccinations required","Influenza only","Pneumococcus only","Pneumococcus and influenza","Pneumococcus, influenza and herpes zoster (Shingrix)"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis 64-year-old woman is immunosuppressed because she is on methotrexate, and this must be considered when deciding her vaccination recommendations. Methotrexate is used for it\u0027s immunomodulating effects in rheumatoid arthritis. It can put patients at risk of leukopenia and thrombocytopenia, affecting a patient\u0027s ability to amount an appropriate immune response (which serves a purpose in an inflammatory condition such as rheumatoid arthritis).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPneumococcal\u003C/strong\u003E: Adults with \u0022at risk\u0022 conditions (including being immunosuppressed), are recommended to have the 13vPCV pneumococcal vaccine (Prevenar13), if not already been given, followed by 2 doses of 23vPPV (Pneumovax23) at appropriate intervals. For a list of which conditions additional pneumococcal vaccination is recommended, along with whether these are funded under the National Immunisation Program see reference 3. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInfluenza\u003C/strong\u003E: It is recommended all individuals over 6 months of age receive the annual influenza vaccination. Thus the influenza vaccination is indicated as the patient has not been vaccinated in the past 5 years.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHerpes Zoster:\u00a0\u003C/strong\u003EAdults who are immunocompromised are recommended to receive a 2-dose schedule of Shingrix, 1\u20132 months apart, for the prevention of herpes zoster and associated complications. Shingrix is recommended for all adults over 50 years of age however it is only funded on the national immunisation program for adults over 65 years of age or those over 18 years of age who are immunocompromised.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["When deciding vaccine recommendations, a patients immunosuppressed state must be taken into account"],"references":["Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Methotrexate (immunomodulator) [Internet], 2022 [Updated 2022; cited 2023 May 12]. Available from:  \u003Chttps://amhonline-amh-net-au.ezproxy.flinders.edu.au/chapters/immunomodulators-antineoplastics/immunosuppressants/corticosteroids/prednisolone-prednisone?menu=hints\u003E","Australian Technical Advisory Group on Immunisation (ATAGI). Australian Immunisation Handbook, Australian Government Department of Health, Canberra; 2018 [cited 2021 Sep 12]. Available from: \u003Cimmunisationhandbook.health.gov.au.\u003E","Australian Government Department of Health and Aged Care. Table: Risk conditions for pneumococcal vaccination and eligibility for NIP funding. The Australian Immunisation Handbook. Available at: https://immunisationhandbook.health.gov.au/resources/tables/table-risk-conditions-for-pneumococcal-vaccination-and-eligibility-for-nip-funding"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90310"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2813"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90310","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/90310"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-07-04T13:45:32+09: